==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Midship
<hw>Mid"ship`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to, or being in,
the middle of a ship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Midship beam</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>the beam
or timber upon which the broadest part of a vessel is formed.</cd> --
<col><b>Midship bend</b></col>, <cd>the broadest frame in a vessel.</cd>
<au>Weale.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Midshipman</ent>⟦br⟧
